long_desc.thetext:
Here's the minimal code that triggers it.
-------------------
public class Main {
	public <T> void test(Result r) {}

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		new Main().test(r -> System.out.println("Hmmm..." + r));
		// works: new Main().test(r -> System.out.println(r));
	}
}

interface Result {
	public void result(Object object);
}

-------------------

Interface Result initially was generic (Result<T>), but I tried to remove complexity and still trigger the bug.

The problem disappears if I remove the type declaration <T> of Main.test

